docker compose up --build


Your services will be available at:

React: http://localhost:3000
Express API: http://localhost:5000
PostgreSQL: localhost:5432
For production-like local hosting

Instead of running the React development server, build the React app and serve it with Express:

cd client
npm run build

Then configure Express to serve the build (or dist) folder. This results in only two containers:

PostgreSQL
Express (serving both the API and the React frontend)

This setup is faster, uses fewer resources, and more closely matches a production deployment while still running completely offline.